<author><name><![CDATA[AllNight]]></name></author>
<updated>2017-05-23T03:12:16-07:00</updated>
<published>2017-05-23T03:12:16-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5070&amp;p=32744#p32744</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5070&amp;p=32744#p32744"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Where can the XP explorer toolbar buttons / icons be fou]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5070&amp;p=32744#p32744"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-size: 210%; line-height: 116%;">BUMP! <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_cool.gif" alt="8-)" title="Cool" /><br /></span><span style="font-size: 100%; line-height: 116%;"><br />I wanted exactly what the original poster of this thread was asking for... the Windows XP Explorer Toolbar icons.<br /><br />I found either dead links, or icons that looked less than perfect (no disrespect to anyone who tried!).<br /><br />So, I made my own. I got them as 1:1 as I could, and I think they look pretty dead on! <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br /><br />Here's the link (it's a download from Google Drive): </span><strong><span style="font-size: 150%; line-height: 116%;"><a href="https://goo.gl/MqSStW" class="postlink">https://goo.gl/MqSStW</a></span></strong><br /><br />The file is also attached to this post! <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /> <br /><br />I bumped the thread because it's a top Google search result and I just wanted for people to be able to find a good result in the future. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br /><br /><blockquote class="editor"><em>From the readme:</em><br /><hr /></blockquote><blockquote class="editor"><span style="font-family:Courier;">These icons are 25x25; the files that are appended _small are 16x16<br /><br />To use the regular 25x25 icons in Classic Shell Explorer, use these settings<br />on the &quot;Toolbar Settings&quot; tab:<br /><br />Big Buttons: Checked<br />Small icon size: 16<br />Large icon size: 25<br />Menu icon size: 16<br />Text is on the side: Unchecked<br />Same size buttons: Checked<br />Resizeable toolbar: Checked<br /><br />Individually specify the regular 25x25 icon files for each toolbar button.<br /><br />If you want to use the _small icons, then UNCHECK the &quot;Big buttons&quot; check box,<br />and individually specify the icons files appended with _small.<br /><br />&#40;If you use 25x25 and uncheck &quot;Big buttons,&quot; or use 16x16 and check &quot;Big<br />buttons,&quot; then the icons will be scaled, reducing image quality.&#41;<br /><br />I recommend the following sites for .ico conversion from png with<br />transparencies:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://image.online-convert.com/convert-to-ico">http://image.online-convert.com/convert-to-ico</a><!-- m --><br /><br />You can use the following site to batch convert 25x25 icons to 16x16 with good<br />quality:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://convertico.com/">http://convertico.com/</a><!-- m --></span></blockquote><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20314">AllNight</a> — Tue May 23, 2017 3:12 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
